            <thetext>IS:

The qx.Mobile Page event &quot;stop&quot; of the current active page is fired after the &quot;start&quot; event of the next active page.

This bug causes a wrong behavior when a developer tries to show a waiting indicator on start method on a page.

The &quot;start&quot; event shows the dialog, but after the page transition ends, the old page fires the &quot;stop&quot; event, which causes any dialog to disappear.

SHOULD:

The &quot;stop&quot; event of the current page should fire before a &quot;start&quot; event of another page.
Only one page can be active at the same time.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
